That's ok, I understand that it is never going to happen. Imagine the problems implementing something like that would cause. I agree with the fact that marriage is a bit of a throwaway thing now.

I suppose making divorce illegal would have the effect of it being less of a joke, however the cost of legal fees etc of a divorce I feel is a good deterrent and I feel such a drastic approach of outright banning divorce would cause more problems than it would fix, as some people are forced into marriages that they now cannot get out of, and also people change meaning you can grow apart and this makes life incredibly difficult for both parties. But maybe making the penalties harsher would be a reasonable comprise.
